113 e. Video games; and
114 f. Exhibits or installations that feature digital
115 media, wearable technology, or other tools that support
116 participants' engagement with new knowledge, skills, or
117 practices;
118 (l) "U.S. Access Board", the independent federal
119 agency created in 1973 that promotes equality for people
120 with disabilities through leadership in accessible design
121 and the development of accessibility guidelines and
122 standards.
