86 are attributed. In such annual report, if the average wage
87 is below the applicable percentage of the county average
88 wage, the qualified company or qualified military project
89 has not maintained the employee insurance as required, if
90 the department after a review determines the qualifying
91 company fails to satisfy other aspects of their notice of
92 intent, including failure to make good faith efforts to
93 employ, at a minimum, commensurate with the percentage of
94 minority populations in the state of Missouri, as reported
95 in the previous decennial census, the following: racial
96 minorities, contractors who are racial minorities, and
