138 depreciable tangible personal property owned or
139 rented and used in this state during the tax
140 period. The average value of all such property
141 shall be determined as provided in chapter 32;
142 (b) The "payroll factor" is a fraction,
143 the numerator of which is the total amount paid
144 during the tax period by the taxpayer for
145 compensation to persons qualifying as retained
146 business facility employees at the retained
147 business facility, and the denominator of which
148 is the total amount paid in this state during
149 the tax period by the taxpayer for
150 compensation. The compensation paid in this
151 state shall be determined as provided in chapter
