133 funds are invested. Any interest and moneys
134 earned on such investments shall be credited to
135 the fund.
136 7. For purposes of this section, the
137 following terms mean:
138 (1) "Trauma-informed approach", an
139 approach that involves understanding and
140 responding to the symptoms of chronic
141 interpersonal trauma and traumatic stress across
142 the lifespan;
143 (2) "Trauma-informed school", a school
144 that:
145 (a) Realizes the widespread impact of
146 trauma and understands potential paths for
147 recovery;
148 (b) Recognizes the signs and symptoms of
149 trauma in students, teachers, and staff;
150 (c) Responds by fully integrating
151 knowledge about trauma into its policies,
152 procedures, and practices; and
153 (d) Seeks to actively resist
154 retraumatization.
155 8. The provisions of this section shall
156 expire December 31, 2019.]
