1 [334.1135. 1. There is hereby established
2 a joint task force to be known as the "Joint
3 Task Force on Radiologic Technologist Licensure".
4 2. The task force shall be composed of the
5 following:
6 (1) Two members of the senate, one of whom
7 shall be appointed by the president pro tempore
8 and one by the minority leader of the senate;
9 (2) Two members of the house of
10 representatives, one of whom shall be appointed
11 by the speaker and one by the minority leader of
12 the house of representatives;
13 (3) A clinic administrator, or his or her
14 designee, appointed by the Missouri Association
15 of Rural Health Clinics;
16 (4) A physician appointed by the Missouri
17 State Medical Association;
18 (5) A pain management physician appointed
19 by the Missouri Society of Anesthesiologists;
20 (6) A radiologic technologist appointed by
21 the Missouri Society of Radiologic Technologists;
22 (7) A nuclear medicine technologist
23 appointed by the Missouri Valley Chapter of the
24 Society of Nuclear Medicine and Molecular
25 Imaging;

SB 889 289
26 (8) An administrator of an ambulatory
27 surgical center appointed by the Missouri
28 Ambulatory Surgical Center Association;
29 (9) A physician appointed by the Missouri
30 Academy of Family Physicians;
31 (10) A certified registered nurse
32 anesthetist appointed by the Missouri
33 Association of Nurse Anesthetists;
34 (11) A physician appointed by the Missouri
35 Radiological Society;
36 (12) The director of the Missouri state
37 board of registration for the healing arts, or
38 his or her designee; and
39 (13) The director of the Missouri state
40 board of nursing, or his or her designee.
41 3. The task force shall review the current
42 status of licensure of radiologic technologists
43 in Missouri and shall develop a plan to address
44 the most appropriate method to protect public
45 safety when radiologic imaging and radiologic
46 procedures are utilized. The plan shall include:
47 (1) An analysis of the risks associated if
48 radiologic technologists are not licensed;
49 (2) The creation of a Radiologic Imaging
50 and Radiation Therapy Advisory Commission;
51 (3) Procedures to address the specific
52 needs of rural health care and the availability
53 of licensed radiologic technologists;
54 (4) Requirements for licensure of
55 radiographers, radiation therapists, nuclear
56 medicine technologists, nuclear medicine
57 advanced associates, radiologist assistants, and
58 limited x-ray machine operators;
59 (5) Reasonable exemptions to licensure;
60 (6) Continuing education and training;
61 (7) Penalty provisions; and
62 (8) Other items that the task force deems
63 relevant for the proper determination of
64 licensure of radiologic technologists in
65 Missouri.
66 4. The task force shall meet within thirty
67 days of its creation and select a chair and vice
68 chair. A majority of the task force shall
69 constitute a quorum, but the concurrence of a

SB 889 290
70 majority of total members shall be required for
71 the determination of any matter within the task
72 force's duties.
73 5. The task force shall be staffed by
74 legislative personnel as is deemed necessary to
75 assist the task force in the performance of its
76 duties.
77 6. The members of the task force shall
78 serve without compensation, but may, subject to
79 appropriation, be entitled to reimbursement for
80 actual and necessary expenses incurred in the
81 performance of their official duties.
82 7. The task force shall submit a full
83 report of its activities, including the plan
84 developed under subsection 3 of this section, to
85 the general assembly on or before January 15,
86 2020. The task force shall send copies of the
87 report to the director of the division of
88 professional registration.]
